00:17:46,765 --> 00:17:50,329
but now we wanna do a few
a few tweaks because now it's 1940...

247
00:17:50,330 --> 00:17:53,149
and drive-in's are all the rage, I mean
they are the hottest thing going...

248
00:17:53,184 --> 00:17:54,821
and I say,
"Dick, we gotta get in on this"...

249
00:17:54,822 --> 00:17:56,042
- and Dick says,
- "Okay"...

250
00:17:56,043 --> 00:18:00,301
and 2 months later we open for business,
McDonald's Famous Barbecue.

251
00:18:00,302 --> 00:18:04,337
24 item menu, uniformed waitresses
bring your food right to the car...

252
00:18:04,338 --> 00:18:07,749
and it goes gang-busters.
We're going great guns!

253
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:10,539
But then... sales start to level off.

254
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:13,770
- The drive-in model as we've learned has
a few built in problems.

255
00:18:13,771 --> 00:18:14,561
Tell me about it.

256
00:18:14,562 --> 00:18:16,569
For starters, there's the customer issue.

257
00:18:16,570 --> 00:18:20,649
Drive-in's tend to attract, shall we say,
a less than desirable clientele.

258
00:18:20,650 --> 00:18:22,715
- Teenagers.
- Hot-rodders and hooligans and...

259
00:18:22,716 --> 00:18:24,853
juvenile deliquents in blue jeans.

260
00:18:24,854 --> 00:18:26,051
And then there's the service.

261
00:18:26,052 --> 00:18:29,664
It takes forever and a day for your food to arrive,
and when it finally does...

262
00:18:29,665 --> 00:18:30,840
- It's usually wrong.
- Yeah.

263
00:18:30,841 --> 00:18:36,098
The car hops are too busy dodging gropes to remember
that you wanted strawberry phospate, not cherry.

264
00:18:36,099 --> 00:18:37,717
- Well that's if they remember it at all.
- And then...

265
00:18:37,718 --> 00:18:41,407
there's the expenses. The huge payroll
due to the large staff required...

266
00:18:41,408 --> 00:18:45,095
- dishes constantly getting broken or stolen.
- Tremendous overhead.

267
00:18:45,096 --> 00:18:49,767
So one day Dick has a realization. He sees
that the bulk of our sales are in only 3 items.

268
00:18:49,768 --> 00:18:53,233
- Hamburgers, french fries, soft-drinks.
- 87%.

269
00:18:53,798 --> 00:18:58,209
So we say to ourselves let's focus on what
sells and that's exactly what we do...

270
00:18:58,210 --> 00:19:01,323
Brisket gone, tamales gone,
but we don't stop there.

271
00:19:01,324 --> 00:19:02,948
We look at everything.

272
00:19:02,949 --> 00:19:05,271
- What else don't we need?
- Turns out quite a lot.

273
00:19:05,272 --> 00:19:08,081
- Car hops.
- Walk up to a window, get your food yourself.

274
00:19:09,106 --> 00:19:11,163
- Dishes.
- All paper packaging, disposable.

275
00:19:11,164 --> 00:19:14,242
Cigarette machines, jukeboxes,
drive out the riff raff.

276
00:19:14,243 --> 00:19:18,289
- Creating a family friendly environment here.
- But that's not enough.

277
00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:18,773
Alright.

278
00:19:18,774 --> 00:19:22,030
See, our whole lives we've piggy-backed
off of other people's ideas...

279
00:19:22,031 --> 00:19:25,187
We wanted something that wasn't
just different. It had to be better.

280
00:19:25,188 --> 00:19:27,752
It needed to be ours.

281
00:19:28,054 --> 00:19:30,626
And that's what brings us
to the biggest cut of all.

282
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:31,777
Which was?

283
00:19:32,854 --> 00:19:36,789
- The wait.
- Orders ready in 30 seconds, not 30 minutes.

284
00:19:37,299 --> 00:19:38,037
Mecca.

285
00:19:38,038 --> 00:19:41,304
- We look at each other one night...
- You thinkin' what I'm thinkin'?

286
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:45,481
We're gonna have to tear down,
rebuild, reconfi... rethink the whole dang thing.

287
00:19:45,482 --> 00:19:49,014
We're talking about shutting
down a thriving business for months.

288
00:19:49,015 --> 00:19:50,128
People are gonna think we're crazy.

289
00:19:51,066 --> 00:19:52,336
We were, crazy.

290
00:19:53,587 --> 00:19:56,306
And you are gonna love how we did it.
Dick, you gotta tell him.

291
00:19:56,307 --> 00:19:59,124
- Tennis court.
- Okay, he brings me out to this tennis court...

292
00:19:59,125 --> 00:20:02,280
and he's drawn this line the
exact dimenions of our kitchen...

293
00:20:02,281 --> 00:20:04,283
Sink on the right, extruder on the left.

294
00:20:04,284 --> 00:20:06,004
Bagging and hood.

295
00:20:06,364 --> 00:20:07,005
Okay. Garnish... this is uh...

296
00:20:07,006 --> 00:20:10,235
- burger finish.
- Got it.

297
00:20:10,236 --> 00:20:11,741
and then this is burger slide.

298
00:20:13,116 --> 00:20:14,632
We could just move those.

299
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:16,866
- Okay.
- Multimixer, soft drinks...

300
00:20:16,867 --> 00:20:20,410
We bring out our whole staff and
we have 'em go through the motions...

301
00:20:20,411 --> 00:20:22,579
making pretend burgers and fries.

302
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:24,763
Alright, Steve, ya gotta
anticipate that...

303
00:20:24,764 --> 00:20:26,612
Ya gotta keep the tray level!

304
00:20:28,428 --> 00:20:31,707
Dick is running around with a stick
marking where all the equipment should be.

305
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:35,722
Tuck in. Tony are you going to skip the
pickles when we're really doing it?

306
00:20:35,723 --> 00:20:40,429
They do it over and over, hashing it out,
choreographing it like some crazy burger ballet.

307
00:20:40,430 --> 00:20:41,461
What's going on over there?

308
00:20:41,465 --> 00:20:42,513
Yes.

309
00:20:43,303 --> 00:20:44,475
No!

310
00:20:44,580 --> 00:20:45,747
NO!

311
00:20:48,060 --> 00:20:49,323
Everybody stop!

312
00:20:50,024 --> 00:20:52,183
Garnish #1.
Garnish #2.

313
00:20:52,184 --> 00:20:54,203
You've got pickles, you've got onions.

314
00:20:55,589 --> 00:20:57,193
It's a goddamn hamburger.

315
00:20:57,194 --> 00:20:59,645
- Come on, clear out.
- Let's clear off.

316
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:01,384
It's time for the pink chalk.

317
00:21:02,462 --> 00:21:03,980
and then rootbeer, orange.

318
00:21:06,186 --> 00:21:08,818
See all this open space here now?

319
00:21:08,819 --> 00:21:11,825
We've rearrange the fry situation so now...

320
00:21:11,826 --> 00:21:12,826
it's stage left, the fryer is stage right.

321
00:21:15,531 --> 00:21:16,741
Again...

322
00:21:16,742 --> 00:21:17,819
That's great.

323
00:21:17,820 --> 00:21:18,753
Come on guys.

324
00:21:18,754 --> 00:21:22,959
- We're pretty tied up here with the Lazy Susan.
- Yeah, watch it. This is the timing if the Lazy Susan...

325
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:26,995
Those are finished burgers!
You can't... hold it!

326
00:21:29,127 --> 00:21:31,160
I still think there's a 3rd version.

327
00:21:31,161 --> 00:21:33,190
- Well, what do you want to move?
- I want to move everything.

328
00:21:33,191 --> 00:21:34,191
To stage left please.

329
00:21:42,668 --> 00:21:43,543
Got it all drawn?

330
00:21:44,208 --> 00:21:45,221
This is better.

331
00:21:45,946 --> 00:21:47,026
Is that alright?

332
00:21:47,264 --> 00:21:48,327
This so.

333
00:21:48,808 --> 00:21:53,055
- I guess... let's assume our battle stations.
- Okay, okay.

334
00:21:54,485 --> 00:21:57,553
Finally...
after about 6 hours of this...

335
00:21:57,554 --> 00:22:02,231
we get it just right. It's a symphony
of efficiency, not a wasted motion.

336
00:22:14,143 --> 00:22:15,606
Good form Jasper!

337
00:22:18,188 --> 00:22:20,854
Feel good about those pickles.
Ketchup!

338
00:22:21,489 --> 00:22:22,762
Use your Lazy Susan.

339
00:22:25,598 --> 00:22:27,751
Put your back into it Seth!

340
00:22:28,011 --> 00:22:31,521
And pickles and pickle and...
mustard!

341
00:22:32,338 --> 00:22:36,311
We take the layout to a builder,
custom build the kitchen to our exact specs.

342
00:22:36,312 --> 00:22:38,940
Ta dah! The speedy system is born.

343
00:22:38,941 --> 00:22:43,421
The world's first ever system to deliver
food fast. It is totally revolutionary...

344
00:22:43,422 --> 00:22:45,179
- and a complete disaster.
- Why?

345
00:22:45,546 --> 00:22:50,129
Opening day, cars pull up onto the lot and they start
honking immediately because no car-hop comes up.

346
00:22:50,130 --> 00:22:51,227
You place your order.

347
00:22:51,228 --> 00:22:54,151
We try to explain to them the walk
up window and they are uh...

348
00:22:54,152 --> 00:22:57,921
bewildered? No, furious.
"What do you mean I gotta get out of my car?"

349
00:22:57,922 --> 00:22:59,797
Most of 'em just cuss us
out and drive off...

350
00:22:59,798 --> 00:23:03,880
and the few that stay are mad as heck because they are
eating off paper and they've gotta discard their own trash.

351
00:23:03,881 --> 00:23:04,474
Why?

352
00:23:04,475 --> 00:23:05,863
You're doing great, you're doing great.

353
00:23:05,864 --> 00:23:07,833
Yeah, we won't be coming out to
the car but you can just come on up.

354
00:23:07,834 --> 00:23:09,170
Welcome to McDonald's.

355
00:23:09,171 --> 00:23:12,197
We may have underestimated the learning curve.

356
00:23:12,198 --> 00:23:13,198
So by 5 o'clock, Dick is calculating how
much it's gonna cost to go back to drive-in...

357
00:23:13,199 --> 00:23:17,492
but I am not ready to throw in the towel.

358
00:23:17,493 --> 00:23:21,779
So I go back to our old Hollywood days, I
think to myself, we gotta go big with this.

359
00:23:21,780 --> 00:23:22,965
We gotta put on a show.

360
00:23:22,966 --> 00:23:25,129
So I say, "Dick, I wanna throw
a grand re-opening...

361
00:23:25,130 --> 00:23:27,460
a gala premeire that would put
Louis B. Mayer to shame.

362
00:23:27,461 --> 00:23:29,356
So we rent a bunch of spotlights...

363
00:23:29,357 --> 00:23:31,401
the ones we used to haul
around in the Columbia days...

364
00:23:31,402 --> 00:23:34,291
we get sparklers, a juggler for the kiddies,
it is an event...

365
00:23:34,326 --> 00:23:37,145
people show up in droves,
and then...

366
00:23:37,753 --> 00:23:38,410
The flies.

367
00:23:38,411 --> 00:23:40,708
They must have been
drawn by all the lights.

368
00:23:40,709 --> 00:23:43,916
Millions of 'em.
It was like a scene out of Exodus.

369
00:23:43,917 --> 00:23:46,213
The pharaoh would have
released the Israelites...

370
00:23:47,438 --> 00:23:49,446
Total disaster.

371
00:23:49,447 --> 00:23:50,447
Now it is 'towel' time.

372
00:23:51,427 --> 00:23:54,788
The next day Dick and I meet up to
discuss going back to the old format.

373
00:23:54,789 --> 00:23:57,414
And as we're talking there's
a knock at the service window...

374
00:24:02,007 --> 00:24:03,462
I tell him we're closed.

375
00:24:03,463 --> 00:24:04,463
- We're closed.
- but he's looked so cute.

376
00:24:04,464 --> 00:24:06,964
Hang on, hang on...

377
00:24:06,965 --> 00:24:09,254
- What would you like son?
- Can I buy a bag of burgers from you?

378
00:24:09,255 --> 00:24:14,169
And I feel bad so I fire up the
grill and I make him a batch...

379
00:24:16,091 --> 00:24:16,976
There you are.

380
00:24:21,017 --> 00:24:23,748
And as he's walking away from the
service window, a car pulls up.

381
00:24:28,463 --> 00:24:29,454
And then another.

382
00:24:33,189 --> 00:24:33,882
Dick...

383
00:24:36,146 --> 00:24:37,095
And then another.

384
00:24:45,716 --> 00:24:47,172
Hello, welcome to McDonald's.

385
00:24:47,173 --> 00:24:48,210
Hello there.

386
00:24:48,211 --> 00:24:50,180
Pretty soon there's a line around the block.

387
00:24:50,181 --> 00:24:52,639
- The word has spread.
- And it's off to the races.

388
00:24:52,640 --> 00:24:55,163
And we are an overnight sensation,
30 years in the making.

389
00:25:03,458 --> 00:25:04,521
So that's our story.

390
00:25:48,552 --> 00:25:49,795
Franchise.

391
00:25:49,796 --> 00:25:51,237
- Beg pardon?
- Franchise.

392
00:25:51,238 --> 00:25:52,887
Franchise the damn thing.

393
00:25:52,888 --> 00:25:54,928
It's too damn good for just one location.

394
00:25:54,929 --> 00:25:58,727
There should be McDonald's everywhere.
Coast to coast, sea to shining sea.

395
00:25:58,728 --> 00:26:02,881
- Mr. Kroc...
- Hey, I got a confession I wanna make to you boys...

396
00:26:04,661 --> 00:26:08,757
I'm not out here in California for any kind
of business meetings. I came out here for you.

397
00:26:08,758 --> 00:26:14,033
A few days ago I got into St. Louis, Missouri and I
was doing some business and I broke out my map.

398
00:26:14,034 --> 00:26:18,734
And I followed my finger on
one single highway, West.

399
00:26:18,958 --> 00:26:21,313
- Route 66. And somethin' told me...
- Mr. Kroc...

400
00:26:21,348 --> 00:26:25,177
Somethin' told me to get into my car and drive
that highway and you know where it led me?

401
00:26:25,617 --> 00:26:27,720
Right here.
Right smack dab here.

402
00:26:27,721 --> 00:26:30,156
Right to this unbelievable establishment...

403
00:26:30,157 --> 00:26:34,242
and when I saw these lines to your home
operation and I tasted your product...

404
00:26:34,243 --> 00:26:36,008
I knew what needed to happen.

405
00:26:36,068 --> 00:26:39,584
Franchising. Franchise, franchise, franchise.

406
00:26:40,570 --> 00:26:41,413
Franchise.

407
00:26:43,624 --> 00:26:45,437
We already tried.

408
00:26:50,751 --> 00:26:55,067
5. Three in Southern California,
one in Sacramento and one in Phoenix...

409
00:26:55,068 --> 00:26:57,043
And that's all there will ever be.

410
00:26:57,471 --> 00:26:58,336
Why?

411
00:26:58,358 --> 00:27:01,232
Two words:
Quality Control.

412
00:27:01,905 --> 00:27:05,135
It's almost impossible to enforce standards from afar.

413
00:27:05,136 --> 00:27:08,332
Places were a mess. Filthy
kitchens, inconsistent menus...

414
00:27:08,333 --> 00:27:10,295
Sacramento was selling burritos.

415
00:27:10,296 --> 00:27:14,350
To watch your precious creation
be mismanaged like that...

416
00:27:14,351 --> 00:27:17,538
- Your name.
- Put Mac in the hospital.

417
00:27:20,125 --> 00:27:23,820
- Well, you put somebody in charge of supervising.
- We did.

418
00:27:24,223 --> 00:27:25,052
So then, what happened?

419
00:27:25,674 --> 00:27:27,616
He obviously didn't do a great job.

420
00:27:27,617 --> 00:27:29,747
So you hire somebody else, get somebody better.

421
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:34,736
Our energies are better spent making
this place the best it can possibly be.

422
00:27:34,737 --> 00:27:37,559
It's better to have one great restaurant
than 50 mediocre ones.

423
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:41,328
- Yeah, yeah. I still think you hire the right guy...
- Ray, we're not interested.

424
00:27:41,329 --> 00:27:44,195
Look, I think you boys are missing
something here that is...

425
00:27:44,196 --> 00:27:46,263
I tell ya, ya gotta...
somethin' here...

426
00:27:48,384 --> 00:27:50,019
Wuh... what is that?

427
00:27:50,670 --> 00:27:52,415
- A concept.
- Huh.

428
00:27:52,416 --> 00:27:53,761
What are those?

429
00:27:53,762 --> 00:27:57,279
Oh, it's a way to make the place
stand out when you're driving by.

430
00:27:57,930 --> 00:27:59,924
The golden arches, I call 'em.

431
00:28:01,116 --> 00:28:03,087
The golden arches...

432
00:28:04,386 --> 00:28:07,352
- Who thought of that?
- Oh that's some pure Dick magic right there.

433
00:28:09,025 --> 00:28:11,049
Did ya ever build one like that?

434
00:28:11,050 --> 00:28:13,895
Just one...
Phoenix.

435
00:29:50,642 --> 00:29:52,100
Ethel?

436
00:29:52,552 --> 00:29:53,252
In here.

437
00:29:53,678 --> 00:29:58,178
Oh boy. I saw a restaurant.
I've never seen a restaurant like this in my life.

438
00:29:58,179 --> 00:30:01,593
They got this fully automated... system.

439
00:30:01,594 --> 00:30:03,966
- It's called the speedy system.
- Mmm hmm.

440
00:30:04,189 --> 00:30:06,647
Which is a good name for
it because man it is speedy.

441
00:30:07,723 --> 00:30:12,661
I tell ya, it's like something sprung
from the mind of Henry Ford or something.

442
00:30:13,369 --> 00:30:15,528
- It's revolutionary?
- It's revolutionary.

443
00:30:15,529 --> 00:30:17,488
That's exactly what it is,
it's revolutionary.

444
00:30:18,105 --> 00:30:20,256
- And you wanna invest in it?
- I don't know.

445
00:30:20,257 --> 00:30:23,247
I don't know. I'm not sure yet.
I just know I want to be a part of it.

446
00:30:24,606 --> 00:30:27,151
- Boy.
- So here we go.

447
00:30:27,961 --> 00:30:29,021
What do you mean by that?

448
00:30:29,755 --> 00:30:33,970
Wax cups, folding nooks, multimixers.
A new idea to chase.

449
00:30:33,971 --> 00:30:36,703
Those things put a roof over our heads.

450
00:30:36,704 --> 00:30:37,884
At least over mine.

451
00:30:37,885 --> 00:30:40,351
What do you mean over yours?
Over our heads...

452
00:30:41,122 --> 00:30:44,198
It's a good roof Ray.
It's a good house.

453
00:30:45,004 --> 00:30:46,789
It's a good life if you
weren't too busy to live it.

454
00:30:47,787 --> 00:30:50,428
We could go to the club more than twice a year.

455
00:30:50,429 --> 00:30:52,851
Christ, just take a walk around the block together.

456
00:30:52,852 --> 00:30:56,467
Isn't time to enjoy a little
and stop chasing your tail?

457
00:30:57,616 --> 00:30:59,507
When's enough gonna be enough for you?

458
00:31:02,016 --> 00:31:04,083
Honestly?

459
00:31:04,084 --> 00:31:05,126
Probably never.

460
00:31:09,148 --> 00:31:11,602
Why should I settle
when other men won't?

461
00:31:11,603 --> 00:31:12,572
I don't know Ray.

462
00:31:12,573 --> 00:31:15,487
Maybe if I had a wife that had an
ounce a vision.

463
00:31:15,488 --> 00:31:17,615
Showed me an ounce of support.

464
00:31:19,102 --> 00:31:20,090
Sorry, wrong word.

465
00:31:20,091 --> 00:31:22,290
I've done nothing but support you.

466
00:31:22,291 --> 00:31:23,024
Oh look, I'm sorry...

467
00:31:23,025 --> 00:31:28,789
- Ups, downs, dwindling savings, your schemes...
- You're right.

468
00:32:58,047 --> 00:33:02,017
Are ya familiar with the concept
of the chicken and the egg Mr. Johnson...

469
00:33:02,018 --> 00:33:03,018
because I think that's applicable here.

470
00:33:54,613 --> 00:33:56,367
Hey Dick...

471
00:33:59,531 --> 00:34:01,553
What is it with this guy?

472
00:34:01,963 --> 00:34:03,834
- Do it for your country.
- What?

473
00:34:07,552 --> 00:34:10,216
If you boys don't want to
franchise for yourselves, that's fine...

474
00:34:10,982 --> 00:34:11,903
Do it for your country.

475
00:34:13,857 --> 00:34:15,094
Do it for America.

476
00:34:20,660 --> 00:34:24,045
Ya know what, I drove through a lot of towns.
A lot of small towns.

477
00:34:24,917 --> 00:34:26,328
And they all had two things in common...

478
00:34:27,355 --> 00:34:29,088
They had a courthouse and they had a church.

479
00:34:29,289 --> 00:34:32,284
On top of the church, got a cross...

480
00:34:32,585 --> 00:34:35,087
and on top of the courthouse they have a flag.

481
00:34:35,429 --> 00:34:39,412
Flags, crosses, crosses flags.

482
00:34:40,067 --> 00:34:44,740
Driving around I just cannot stop thinking
about this tremendous restaurant.

483
00:34:44,741 --> 00:34:47,550
Now at the risk of sounding blasphemous...

484
00:34:47,551 --> 00:34:48,955
forgive me.

485
00:34:50,061 --> 00:34:52,476
Those arches have a lot in common
with those buildings.

486
00:34:52,992 --> 00:34:56,604
A building with a cross on top, what is that?
It's a gathering place...

487
00:34:56,605 --> 00:35:03,293
where decent wholesome people come together
and they share values protected by that American flag.

488
00:35:03,994 --> 00:35:08,052
It could be said that that beautiful
building flanked by those arches...

489
00:35:09,462 --> 00:35:12,180
signifies more or less the same thing.

490
00:35:12,181 --> 00:35:15,478
It doesn't just say,
"Delicious hamburgers inside"...

491
00:35:16,703 --> 00:35:22,093
They signify family. It signifies community.
It's a place where Americans come together to break bread.

492
00:35:22,094 --> 00:35:23,576
I am telling you...

493
00:35:25,576 --> 00:35:30,793
McDonald's can be...
the new American church.

494
00:35:32,005 --> 00:35:36,576
Feeding bodies and feeding souls
and it ain't just open on Sundays, boys.

495
00:35:37,976 --> 00:35:40,009
It's open 7 days a week.

496
00:35:47,742 --> 00:35:50,886
Crosses...
Flags...

497
00:35:51,853 --> 00:35:53,044
Arches.

498
00:36:01,042 --> 00:36:02,725
Give us a minute Ray.

499
00:36:02,726 --> 00:36:04,653
Sure.

500
00:36:08,721 --> 00:36:09,887
I don't know.

501
00:36:10,710 --> 00:36:14,109
This is your dream.
It's bigger than your dream.

502
00:36:14,110 --> 00:36:15,843
Arches. Your arches...

503
00:36:16,485 --> 00:36:17,584
coast to coast.

504
00:36:19,004 --> 00:36:21,011
I can't put you through that again.

505
00:36:21,507 --> 00:36:23,158
I know how bad you want this...

506
00:36:23,159 --> 00:36:25,360
- and you should have it.
- Your diabetes...

507
00:36:25,361 --> 00:36:27,655
- Last time...
- We'll do things differently.

508
00:36:27,656 --> 00:36:28,635
We'll learn from our mistakes.

509
00:36:28,636 --> 00:36:30,653
- How so?
- Keep a tighter leash on everything.

510
00:36:30,654 --> 00:36:32,019
Complete oversight.

511
00:36:32,020 --> 00:36:34,043
Every change goes through us.

512
00:36:34,044 --> 00:36:35,656
Who says he's gonna listen?

513
00:36:36,247 --> 00:36:37,608
We'll make him listen.

514
00:36:37,609 --> 00:36:41,333
Draw up a contract.
Clear as day. Black and white.

515
00:37:03,156 --> 00:37:03,959
Fine.

516
00:37:07,875 --> 00:37:08,472
Fine.

517
00:37:12,950 --> 00:37:14,496
Fine.

518
00:37:15,257 --> 00:37:15,788
Fine.

519
00:37:20,274 --> 00:37:21,521
Fine.

520
00:37:39,632 --> 00:37:40,817
Let's get to work boys.

521
00:37:40,818 --> 00:37:42,165
What's the first step?

522
00:37:42,166 --> 00:37:43,262
Just leave that to me.

523
00:37:43,647 --> 00:37:48,814
We are a dynamic fast-growing company and
we're poised to make major in-roads nationally...

524
00:37:48,815 --> 00:37:52,374
So in addition to giving us a real strong
foothold right here in the Midwest...

525
00:37:52,375 --> 00:37:57,801
to display it's location with service as a
kind of a lure for other franchises if you will.

526
00:37:57,802 --> 00:37:59,243
What are those?

527
00:38:01,039 --> 00:38:02,528
- What are...
- Those.

528
00:38:06,578 --> 00:38:08,748
Lemme see... oh those, yeah...

529
00:38:08,749 --> 00:38:12,144
That's just my little way of separating
us from the rest of the pack.

530
00:38:12,973 --> 00:38:16,245
Yah like 'em?
I call 'em The Golden Arches.

531
00:38:17,089 --> 00:38:18,837
You look familiar.
Have we met before?

532
00:38:19,899 --> 00:38:21,957
I don't think so... no.
I think I'd remember that.

533
00:38:22,297 --> 00:38:24,887
Peruse the inside of your...
if you don't mind.

534
00:38:24,888 --> 00:38:27,014
Take a look... yeah,
read that.

535
00:38:27,601 --> 00:38:28,633
The fold-a-nook.

536
00:38:29,597 --> 00:38:31,855
It's like a Murphy bed for your kitchen.

537
00:38:32,165 --> 00:38:32,714
Huh?

538
00:38:36,841 --> 00:38:40,040
Take look at the blueprints,
here we are.

539
00:38:40,701 --> 00:38:41,991
We had those done locally.

540
00:38:41,992 --> 00:38:43,512
Yeah, I never forget a face.

541
00:38:49,623 --> 00:38:52,040
Unique, original, totally innovative...

542
00:38:52,041 --> 00:38:55,713
There's nothing like this. Nothing.
In the entire food service sector.

543
00:38:56,285 --> 00:38:59,040
Nice brochure,
professionally done.

544
00:39:01,908 --> 00:39:02,940
Have we met?

545
00:39:04,537 --> 00:39:06,120
The paper cup guy.

546
00:39:06,525 --> 00:39:08,450
Yeah.
That was a long time ago.

547
00:39:09,756 --> 00:39:11,171
That was a long time ago...

548
00:39:12,997 --> 00:39:14,012
What do you think?

549
00:39:14,653 --> 00:39:15,617
I don't know.

550
00:39:18,549 --> 00:39:23,261
There's...
Look...

551
00:39:25,553 --> 00:39:27,921
I'm gonna level with ya, uh...

552
00:39:30,879 --> 00:39:32,208
I need this one.

553
00:39:32,998 --> 00:39:36,339
Do ya think...
Is there anything you can do to help me out?

554
00:39:36,340 --> 00:39:38,702
I'll tell ya what.
Lemme refer ya to one of my colleagues.

555
00:39:39,348 --> 00:39:42,150
Somebody who may be better
suited to meet your needs.

556
00:39:43,095 --> 00:39:45,472
Thank you.

557
00:39:49,532 --> 00:39:51,974
Ray Kroc...
Address?

558
00:39:52,115 --> 00:39:55,346
143, Juniper Road.

559
00:39:56,229 --> 00:39:58,457
Arlington Heights, Illinois.

560
00:40:00,298 --> 00:40:01,335
Home telephone number?

561
00:40:02,782 --> 00:40:07,034
Ah... use my office telephone number.
That's the place to reach me.

562
00:40:08,182 --> 00:40:09,120
Alright.

563
00:40:09,888 --> 00:40:13,054
Of course we'll need an appraisal on your
home before we can issue funds.

564
00:40:38,199 --> 00:40:39,299
Be right.

565
00:40:41,238 --> 00:40:42,474
Just be right one time.

566
00:40:58,051 --> 00:40:59,289
One time.

567
00:41:01,468 --> 00:41:04,039
- June, did you schedule the stake out with the engineer?
- All set.

568
00:41:04,040 --> 00:41:06,507
What about the fire department?
Did you get the approval for the driveway design?

569
00:41:06,508 --> 00:41:08,352
Left a message with them yesterday.

570
00:41:08,353 --> 00:41:11,121
- Excavation permits?
- I'm meeting with them today.

571
00:41:11,534 --> 00:41:12,432
All right.

572
00:41:12,635 --> 00:41:15,465
Hey, what's going on with
San Bernardino by the way?

573
00:41:15,714 --> 00:41:19,330
I just spoke to Dick,
he said they're working on it.

574
00:41:20,611 --> 00:41:21,643
They're working on it...

575
00:41:22,007 --> 00:41:23,362
That's what he said.

576
00:41:25,036 --> 00:41:26,445
Ray Kroc on the line.

577
00:41:30,356 --> 00:41:33,209
- Hi Ray.
- Boy, you boys are killin' me.

578
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:35,930
What's the old up?
I break ground in 2 weeks.

579
00:41:35,931 --> 00:41:39,985
These things take time and
you're proposing substantial alterations.

580
00:41:39,986 --> 00:41:42,600
I'm adding a basement and a furnace,
that's all.

581
00:41:42,601 --> 00:41:47,242
We need our architect to thoroughly review it
and make sure everything is safe and up to code.

582
00:41:47,243 --> 00:41:49,928
Fine, has he seen it yet?
Has he taken a look at it?

583
00:41:50,322 --> 00:41:51,601
I'm not sure to be honest.

584
00:41:51,602 --> 00:41:54,678
I've got bulldozers rolling up
on the 23rd.

585
00:41:54,679 --> 00:41:56,221
I'm not the one who scheduled that.

586
00:41:56,222 --> 00:41:58,627
Ray, I need you to take a breath.

587
00:41:58,628 --> 00:42:01,989
Take a breath...
Do you realize what it's going to cost me if I have to push?

588
00:42:02,697 --> 00:42:04,057
Hopefully it won't come to that.

589
00:42:04,058 --> 00:42:07,805
Every restaurant in the Midwest has a basement
and a furnance.

590
00:42:07,806 --> 00:42:08,805
This is standard stuff.

591
00:42:08,806 --> 00:42:11,203
I understand, but it's our
name on that building.

592
00:42:11,582 --> 00:42:17,370
God forbid the floor caves in and people get hurt,
or worse, because of some design flaw we missed.

593
00:42:17,371 --> 00:42:20,379
Let's just slow down a minute
and make sure it's done right.

594
00:42:20,380 --> 00:42:22,025
So much for the speedy system, huh?

595
00:42:27,694 --> 00:42:29,849
- Did he just hang up on you?
- Yes.

596
00:42:30,596 --> 00:42:32,868
Unless we got violently disconnected.

597
00:42:33,312 --> 00:42:33,879
Okay...

598
00:42:36,384 --> 00:42:37,513
He'll be fine.

599
00:42:40,092 --> 00:42:43,335
Where's the front of the uh... show me.

600
00:42:44,926 --> 00:42:45,417
Alright.

601
00:42:45,418 --> 00:42:49,526
Just make sure the windows are big enough so that the
customer can look in to the restaurant, all the way to the kitchen.

602
00:42:49,786 --> 00:42:51,339
Doesn't look right.
Let's see this...

603
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:51,975
- Ray?
- What?

604
00:42:51,976 --> 00:42:53,722
We got a letter from San Bernardino.

605
00:42:54,380 --> 00:42:55,352
Read it to me.

606
00:42:56,090 --> 00:43:01,040
Dear Ray, thank you for your letter sharing your
idea to strike a deal with Coca-Cola...

607
00:43:01,041 --> 00:43:04,533
to sponsor menu boards at
the new Des Plaines location.

608
00:43:05,004 --> 00:43:06,942
An intriguing notion indeed.

609
00:43:07,765 --> 00:43:09,133
As you rightly point out...

610
00:43:09,134 --> 00:43:14,033
such an arrangement would provide a steady source
of revenue to the store at no additional labor cost.

611
00:43:14,816 --> 00:43:16,269
- However...
- However?

612
00:43:16,811 --> 00:43:17,371
However what?

613
00:43:18,511 --> 00:43:23,796
However this goes beyond our core beliefs.
McDonald's was founded with the idea...

614
00:43:25,126 --> 00:43:27,801
- of families and not strict commerce.
- Son of a bitch.

615
00:43:27,802 --> 00:43:30,552
- They dunno what they're talkin' about.
- And so on and so on...

616
00:43:32,999 --> 00:43:34,400
There ya go gentlemen.

617
00:43:34,608 --> 00:43:35,579
Back to work.

618
00:43:35,580 --> 00:43:36,418
Lemme explain.

619
00:43:36,419 --> 00:43:39,645
Be real small, right across the bottom.
Very discreet.

620
00:43:39,646 --> 00:43:43,906
We're just not comfortable with the notion
of turning our menu into an advertisement.

621
00:43:43,907 --> 00:43:46,538
See, it's not an ad,
it's sponsorship.

622
00:43:46,539 --> 00:43:47,746
It's distasteful.

623
00:43:47,747 --> 00:43:48,751
It's free money!

624
00:43:48,752 --> 00:43:52,361
There are plenty of things we could do to
make a quick buck. That doesn't mean we should.

625
00:43:52,362 --> 00:43:54,277
- Loads of restaurants do this.
- Well we don't.

626
00:43:54,278 --> 00:43:54,869
Why not?

627
00:43:54,870 --> 00:43:58,821
Because I have no interest in indulging
in that sort of crass commercialism.

628
00:43:58,822 --> 00:44:00,020
It's not McDonald's.

629
00:44:00,021 --> 00:44:02,338
I didn't realize I was parterning
with a beatnik.

630
00:44:02,339 --> 00:44:04,910
I'll have you know I'm a card
carrying Republican!

631
00:44:04,911 --> 00:44:06,309
Yeah, well you coulda fooled me.

632
00:44:07,513 --> 00:44:08,953
He hung up again.

633
00:44:09,357 --> 00:44:12,337
Well he's just a little excitable,
that's all.

634
00:44:15,939 --> 00:44:19,061
A hothead like that,
you don't know what he's capable of.

635
00:44:19,062 --> 00:44:22,280
It's all bluster Dick.
His bark is worse than his bite.

636
00:44:22,759 --> 00:44:25,722
- That's what Neville Chamberlain said.
- He'll relax...

637
00:44:25,941 --> 00:44:26,969
Give him some time.

638
00:44:34,394 --> 00:44:36,912
What are doin', come on!
There's time to lean, there's time to clean.

639
00:44:37,083 --> 00:44:37,720
Let's go.

640
00:44:39,947 --> 00:44:41,247
Put that hat on straight.

641
00:44:44,990 --> 00:44:47,859
400 degrees, right?
That a boy, way to work.

642
00:44:47,936 --> 00:44:48,964
Nice.

643
00:44:49,656 --> 00:44:52,713
Hey, there's one pickle on there.
2 pickles on all the buns.

644
00:44:52,714 --> 00:44:53,899
2 pickles on all of 'em.

645
00:44:54,268 --> 00:44:56,080
Don't... don't.
Look watch.

646
00:44:56,081 --> 00:44:58,509
Flip 'em like that. Really turn 'em over and
then press 'em one time.

647
00:44:58,510 --> 00:44:59,509
And that one's too pink.

648
00:44:59,435 --> 00:45:00,535
There, all right?

649
00:45:01,256 --> 00:45:07,986
Wait... and you...
get these...

650
00:45:09,622 --> 00:45:10,994
Pretty damn good.

651
00:45:11,058 --> 00:45:12,807
- What's your name?
- Fred Turner sir.

652
00:45:14,415 --> 00:45:15,374
Nice work.

653
00:45:15,375 --> 00:45:16,275
Fred Turner.

654
00:45:16,903 --> 00:45:17,764
Fred Turner.

655
00:46:03,647 --> 00:46:04,751
I'm sorry.

656
00:46:05,886 --> 00:46:08,248
I know I've been neglecting you.

657
00:46:16,544 --> 00:46:20,941
What do you say tomorrow...
we go to supper at the club?

658
00:46:27,670 --> 00:46:28,821
Really?

659
00:46:29,292 --> 00:46:30,214
Really.

660
00:46:34,238 --> 00:46:36,098
Well look what the cat dragged in.

661
00:46:36,099 --> 00:46:38,398
Hey everybody.
Hi there. Hey.

662
00:46:38,399 --> 00:46:39,399
- How are ya?
- Good evening stranger.

663
00:46:42,946 --> 00:46:45,644
This is on the left side of the 14th fairway.

664
00:46:45,645 --> 00:46:47,553
- And I use a 3 wood.
- Hmm.

665
00:46:47,554 --> 00:46:50,581
- Hit it clean.
- I hear Acapulco is divine.

666
00:46:50,803 --> 00:46:51,957
Where do you like Ethel?

667
00:46:51,958 --> 00:46:54,433
Um... Spain.

668
00:46:54,434 --> 00:46:55,608
Spain?

669
00:46:55,609 --> 00:46:57,555
Wonderful. How was it?

670
00:46:57,918 --> 00:47:01,668
- Oh no, I mean I'm thinkin' about it.
- Oh you haven't been.

671
00:47:01,669 --> 00:47:03,860
Well we're dreaming up a trip.

672
00:47:03,861 --> 00:47:04,848
Right?

673
00:47:06,397 --> 00:47:07,775
- Great.
- Yeah.

674
00:47:10,817 --> 00:47:12,902
- How's your game Ray?
- Lately?

675
00:47:13,955 --> 00:47:14,803
Non-existent.

676
00:47:14,804 --> 00:47:21,501
- I know, been holdin' myself.
- No kidding.

677
00:47:17,810 --> 00:47:21,805
Ha ha, yeah.
I did hit a hole in one of a sort recently though.

678
00:47:23,529 --> 00:47:27,099
I came across a really, really
interesting business opportunity.

679
00:47:27,492 --> 00:47:28,514
Really interesting.

680
00:47:28,515 --> 00:47:30,316
You boys are gonna want a piece of this.

681
00:47:30,317 --> 00:47:32,635
- Here we go again.
- What is it this time Ray?

682
00:47:32,636 --> 00:47:33,637
Restaurant.

683
00:47:34,940 --> 00:47:36,839
- New kind of restaurant.
- New how?

684
00:47:37,202 --> 00:47:39,683
Restaurant filled with milkshakes and fold-a-nooks?

685
00:47:43,793 --> 00:47:44,647
Fold-a-nook...

686
00:47:47,920 --> 00:47:49,694
I'm just jokin' with ya Ray.

687
00:47:49,695 --> 00:47:51,085
Hold on Jack.

688
00:47:51,086 --> 00:47:52,249
You should hear him out.

689
00:47:53,797 --> 00:47:55,248
This one's different.

690
00:47:59,994 --> 00:48:02,424
Well... do tell us more.

691
00:48:03,586 --> 00:48:04,514
I will.

692
00:48:05,301 --> 00:48:06,851
This is a thing of beauty.

693
00:48:08,320 --> 00:48:10,910
Fully automated kitchen, the likes
of which I've never seen...

694
00:48:10,911 --> 00:48:11,850
It's revolutionary.

695
00:48:12,394 --> 00:48:13,215
It's called the speedy system.

696
00:48:13,216 --> 00:48:15,477
The thing I like about this is it's franchiseable.

697
00:48:15,502 --> 00:48:17,834
The first one's already up and running.
Come over and take a look.

698
00:48:17,882 --> 00:48:19,695
It might make you boys a few dollars.

699
00:48:24,495 --> 00:48:25,483
You don't have to worry about a thing...

700
00:48:25,484 --> 00:48:26,887
we're in charge of everything...

701
00:48:26,888 --> 00:48:29,623
and all these franchises look exactly the same.

702
00:48:29,764 --> 00:48:34,149
I'd have never thought it would work,
...(inaudible)...

703
00:48:34,239 --> 00:48:38,448
Easy as pie. You just pay the
franchise fee, we take care of everything else.

704
00:48:42,849 --> 00:48:44,229
Close enough!
Pick it up troop.

705
00:48:44,230 --> 00:48:45,650
Alright, let's do this.

706
00:48:49,179 --> 00:48:52,001
Got her? Ok.
Gonna be real happy here.

707
00:48:56,207 --> 00:48:57,721
- Congratulations.
- Right.

708
00:49:05,441 --> 00:49:07,551
3 new franchises in the last month.

709
00:49:08,121 --> 00:49:09,073
Well that's great.

710
00:49:10,396 --> 00:49:10,946
What?

711
00:49:11,613 --> 00:49:12,594
I don't know...

712
00:49:13,773 --> 00:49:14,446
What?

713
00:49:14,447 --> 00:49:18,814
Don't you think maybe given our experience
that this is all happening a little too quickly?

714
00:49:19,944 --> 00:49:23,613
If they all pop up at once,
how's he gonna maintain standards?

715
00:50:18,235 --> 00:50:19,695
Son of a bitch.

716
00:50:22,690 --> 00:50:24,036
Give it a whack, Jack.

717
00:50:27,216 --> 00:50:28,035
Hey!

718
00:50:28,656 --> 00:50:29,528
- What's goin' on here?
- Look at this.

719
00:50:29,529 --> 00:50:30,756
What is this? Huh?

720
00:50:31,322 --> 00:50:33,426
- What is that?
- It appears to be a hamburger.

721
00:50:33,427 --> 00:50:34,527
Not a McDonald's burger it's not.

722
00:50:34,528 --> 00:50:35,592
Look at all that ketchup.

723
00:50:35,593 --> 00:50:37,364
And you got 3 pickles on
there instead of 2...

724
00:50:37,365 --> 00:50:39,500
and look at that... lettuce.

725
00:50:39,501 --> 00:50:41,737
- Really Jack, lettuce...
- Can we talk about this another time?

726
00:50:41,934 --> 00:50:44,885
Look at this paddy itself.
It is tragically over-cooked.

727
00:50:44,886 --> 00:50:46,970
- Tragically.
- I don't know Ray, it looks good to me.

728
00:50:46,971 --> 00:50:48,391
What the hell do you know about quality?

729
00:50:48,392 --> 00:50:50,871
- I was by your restaurant today too.
- Yeah? What about it?

730
00:50:50,872 --> 00:50:54,522
- Yah got corn on the cob, yah got fried chicken...
