01:06:38,985 --> 01:06:41,330
- And they're looking for a business they can operate together.
- Uh huh, uh huh.

982
01:06:41,331 --> 01:06:44,727
- And they seem very excited.
- Yeah, forget that. Everything's changed.

983
01:06:45,819 --> 01:06:46,448
Ya want a drink?

984
01:06:46,449 --> 01:06:47,799
No, changed how?

985
01:06:49,063 --> 01:06:51,631
Forget the Chicago suburbs, think bigger.

986
01:06:52,347 --> 01:06:54,560
- Bigger...
- I'm not chasing them anymore.

987
01:06:54,855 --> 01:06:56,294
They're chasing me now.

988
01:06:57,296 --> 01:07:01,835
The trip.
How was it?

989
01:07:01,836 --> 01:07:02,868
Triumphant.

990
01:07:03,746 --> 01:07:06,929
They were rolling out the red carpet.
And kissing this ring.

991
01:07:07,385 --> 01:07:09,433
They're begging me for McDonald's now.

992
01:07:09,434 --> 01:07:11,115
Here, have a drink.

993
01:07:14,041 --> 01:07:16,464
- That's nice.
- Yeah, sure is.

994
01:07:18,470 --> 01:07:19,490
I'm sure.

995
01:07:21,913 --> 01:07:27,383
Well, then, all hail...
Pope Raymond I.

996
01:07:30,243 --> 01:07:31,062
Damn right.

997
01:07:33,868 --> 01:07:35,195
Goddamn right.

998
01:07:39,599 --> 01:07:41,300
- Ray?
- Yeah.

999
01:07:41,799 --> 01:07:43,429
We have a small problem.

1000
01:07:43,790 --> 01:07:46,816
Wait a minute...
How can we be almost out of capital?

1001
01:07:46,817 --> 01:07:49,884
Well, your revenue, the
monthly cut of the store's...

1002
01:07:49,753 --> 01:07:51,348
1.4% of debt.

1003
01:07:51,672 --> 01:07:52,700
- 1.4?
- Yeah.

1004
01:07:53,236 --> 01:07:55,765
1.9 minus Dick and Mac's half percent.

1005
01:07:58,901 --> 01:08:00,815
Mr. McDonald, Ray Kroc's on the line.

1006
01:08:04,244 --> 01:08:05,049
Good to see you.

1007
01:08:08,925 --> 01:08:10,899
- Hi Ray.
- I wanna renegotiate.

1008
01:08:10,900 --> 01:08:12,130
Renegotiate what?

1009
01:08:12,131 --> 01:08:13,636
My deal.
My lousy deal.

1010
01:08:13,637 --> 01:08:17,680
1.4 doesn't cover my monthly nut
let alone drive expansion.

1011
01:08:17,681 --> 01:08:19,636
- Ray, those are the terms.
- It's not good enough.

1012
01:08:19,637 --> 01:08:22,638
- It's almost triple our cut.
- Well, you should be getting more too then.

1013
01:08:22,639 --> 01:08:23,408
Shouldn't ya.

1014
01:08:23,409 --> 01:08:24,465
We're not greedy men.

1015
01:08:24,466 --> 01:08:25,572
Greed has nothing to do with it.

1016
01:08:25,573 --> 01:08:28,957
If I had more money to work with
I could be growing this thing at twice the pace.

1017
01:08:28,958 --> 01:08:31,116
- We have no beef with the current rate of expansion.
- I have nothing.

1018
01:08:31,117 --> 01:08:32,632
Not one location in Pennsylvania.

1019
01:08:32,633 --> 01:08:33,857
Nothing in New York.

1020
01:08:33,858 --> 01:08:36,628
- All in good time.
- Nothing in Texas.

1021
01:08:35,809 --> 01:08:36,679
I have no doubt it'll come.

1022
01:08:36,680 --> 01:08:39,068
Ya know, I'm out here breaking
my neck for you guys...

1023
01:08:39,069 --> 01:08:40,493
And you're doing a bang up job.

1024
01:08:40,494 --> 01:08:42,908
Well then I should be doing a hell of
a lot better than just breaking even.

1025
01:08:43,249 --> 01:08:45,341
- I don't know what to say.
- Say you'll renegotiate.

1026
01:08:45,342 --> 01:08:46,536
- I can't.
- Can't or won't?

1027
01:08:46,537 --> 01:08:49,566
Upping your cut, it would be unfair
to the franchisees.

1028
01:08:49,567 --> 01:08:53,725
The franchisees are doing just fine,
I'm the one that's drowning here.

1029
01:08:53,726 --> 01:08:57,003
You freely and willingly agreed
to the terms of your deal, Ray.

1030
01:08:57,004 --> 01:08:58,652
Nobody put a gun to your head.

1031
01:08:59,646 --> 01:09:00,526
- 4%
- No.

1032
01:09:01,192 --> 01:09:03,400
- 3 1/2%
- Ray...

1033
01:09:03,401 --> 01:09:04,253
- What?
- No.

1034
01:09:04,254 --> 01:09:05,379
Goddamn it!

1035
01:09:12,625 --> 01:09:14,263
Dick...

1036
01:09:14,200 --> 01:09:16,202
Is he a pain in the rear?
Yes.

1037
01:09:16,203 --> 01:09:18,007
Does he have a few screws loose,
you bet...

1038
01:09:18,008 --> 01:09:19,842
but that doesn't mean he's
gonna do us any harm.

1039
01:09:19,843 --> 01:09:22,070
- How long are you gonna keep this up Mac?
- Keep up what?

1040
01:09:22,071 --> 01:09:23,838
The whole, Everything Is Fine act.

1041
01:09:23,839 --> 01:09:26,466
There's a wolf in the hen house.
We let him in.

1042
01:09:26,888 --> 01:09:28,452
I never should have listened.

1043
01:09:28,453 --> 01:09:30,670
We have a contract for just
this sort of thing, Dick.

1044
01:09:30,671 --> 01:09:31,919
Should have trusted my gut.

1045
01:09:33,563 --> 01:09:34,972
So it's my fault, huh?

1046
01:09:36,854 --> 01:09:37,901
Just like the movie theater.

1047
01:09:37,902 --> 01:09:40,413
Well I'm sorry.
I wanted you to have your dream.

1048
01:10:01,188 --> 01:10:03,003
$94.00

1049
01:10:06,321 --> 01:10:08,797
It's unbelievable what these suckers cost to run.

1050
01:10:10,475 --> 01:10:12,796
You know my Pop used
to own an ice cream parlor?

1051
01:10:13,459 --> 01:10:15,513
He went belly up from
the refridgeration costs.

1052
01:10:16,075 --> 01:10:17,155
Really?

1053
01:10:32,341 --> 01:10:33,865
A man called today.

1054
01:10:39,652 --> 01:10:41,591
Illinois First Federal.

1055
01:10:46,772 --> 01:10:48,236
Did he say what he wanted?

1056
01:10:48,237 --> 01:10:49,394
Why don't you tell me.

1057
01:10:49,395 --> 01:10:50,259
What did he want?

1058
01:10:52,891 --> 01:10:53,612
Ray...

1059
01:10:53,775 --> 01:10:54,537
What?

1060
01:10:57,864 --> 01:10:59,972
Did you mortgage our home?

1061
01:11:02,616 --> 01:11:04,452
We could lose everything.

1062
01:11:31,529 --> 01:11:35,388
I specifically said the office
is the best place to reach me.

1063
01:11:35,474 --> 01:11:38,000
I tried you there Mr. Kroc,
numerous times.

1064
01:11:38,001 --> 01:11:40,214
You have no right to call me at my home.

1065
01:11:40,579 --> 01:11:44,390
- That's a blatant invasion of my privacy.
- With all due respect sir, when you're...

1066
01:11:44,391 --> 01:11:48,532
3 months behind on your payments you don't
get to pick and choose where we contact you.

1067
01:12:56,252 --> 01:12:58,815
- Ray.
- Surprise inspection.

1068
01:13:00,236 --> 01:13:01,251
What are you doing here?

1069
01:13:04,330 --> 01:13:06,095
I just came up to see how thing's are goin'.

1070
01:13:10,503 --> 01:13:12,649
$12,400.00

1071
01:13:12,922 --> 01:13:15,028
That's a pretty good haul for month #1.
Could be bigger.

1072
01:13:15,551 --> 01:13:18,372
- I hate to mix business with pleasure...
- I don't.

1073
01:13:19,392 --> 01:13:21,623
but, my expenses.

1074
01:13:21,624 --> 01:13:22,025
What about 'em?

1075
01:13:22,026 --> 01:13:24,255
Well they're a bit higher than I anticipated.

1076
01:13:24,256 --> 01:13:25,824
One thing in particular...

1077
01:13:25,825 --> 01:13:29,252
the walk-in. That bill
is a real whopper.

1078
01:13:29,253 --> 01:13:32,143
I don't know, it's a problem,
all that ice cream...

1079
01:13:33,038 --> 01:13:36,717
I don't wanna over step my bounds here,
but I may have found a solution.

1080
01:13:36,730 --> 01:13:38,629
Well Joan did, actually.

1081
01:13:41,148 --> 01:13:42,493
Ya don't say.

1082
01:13:43,504 --> 01:13:47,562
What if I told you there was a way,
all of your owner operators could save...

1083
01:13:47,563 --> 01:13:50,165
literally hundreds of dollars
a year in electrical costs...

1084
01:13:50,166 --> 01:13:54,181
and reduce the time that it
takes to make a milkshake, by half.

1085
01:13:55,280 --> 01:13:56,282
I'll bite.

1086
01:14:07,001 --> 01:14:08,683
It's a powdered milkshake.

1087
01:14:10,530 --> 01:14:13,900
Costs a fraction of ice cream and
there's no refridgeration necessary.

1088
01:14:14,484 --> 01:14:15,712
It contains powdered milk.

1089
01:14:15,713 --> 01:14:19,281
Thickening agents and emulsifiers
simulate the texture of ice cream.

1090
01:14:19,782 --> 01:14:22,250
- Tastes just like the real thing.
- It's easy as pie to make.

1091
01:14:22,251 --> 01:14:25,064
You put a packet into a
glass of water and stir it.

1092
01:14:25,254 --> 01:14:28,251
I know it may be a tad blasphemous
what with your dairy background and all.

1093
01:14:28,252 --> 01:14:31,008
Personally, I think it's
a marvelous idea.

1094
01:14:34,490 --> 01:14:37,393
Chocolate or vanilla?

1095
01:14:37,798 --> 01:14:38,927
Vanilla.

1096
01:15:00,723 --> 01:15:02,867
Good things come to those who wait.

1097
01:15:27,014 --> 01:15:28,294
What do you think?

1098
01:15:28,582 --> 01:15:31,343
I think I'm drinking a
delicious vanilla milkshake.

1099
01:15:34,341 --> 01:15:35,758
May I?

1100
01:15:44,569 --> 01:15:45,595
I can't resist.

1101
01:15:46,150 --> 01:15:47,611
So what do you say?

1102
01:15:47,896 --> 01:15:51,528
- We try it out at our place and if it goes well...
- We roll it out nationally.

1103
01:15:52,659 --> 01:15:54,957
I could, yeah.
Let me think about it.

1104
01:15:58,466 --> 01:15:59,494
You're the boss.

1105
01:16:08,539 --> 01:16:09,559
McDonald's.

1106
01:16:09,560 --> 01:16:12,717
Just found a way to save you,
me and all our owner operators...

1107
01:16:12,718 --> 01:16:16,574
- literally hundreds of dollars a year in electrical costs.
- And what would that be?

1108
01:16:16,575 --> 01:16:18,122
Two words: powerded milkshake.

1109
01:16:18,123 --> 01:16:22,082
I'm tellin' you I came across a remarkable
called instamix.

1110
01:16:22,083 --> 01:16:23,933
Like I say, it's a powdered milkshake,

1111
01:16:23,934 --> 01:16:28,228
it's a fraction of the cost of ice cream
and requires no refridgeration.

1112
01:16:28,229 --> 01:16:29,537
- Ray...
- I tell ya I tried it myself,

1113
01:16:29,538 --> 01:16:31,686
it tastes just like the real thing.
It's delicious!

1114
01:16:31,687 --> 01:16:33,584
Comes in chocolate, comes in vanilla...

1115
01:16:33,585 --> 01:16:34,908
me, I'm a vanilla man.

1116
01:16:34,909 --> 01:16:38,644
Ray we have no interest in a milkshake
that contains NO MILK.

1117
01:16:38,645 --> 01:16:40,925
Why don't we add sawdust to
the hamburgers while we're at it...

1118
01:16:40,926 --> 01:16:42,205
frozen french fries.

1119
01:16:42,206 --> 01:16:44,584
- You don't want to save a bundle.
- Not like that.

1120
01:16:44,585 --> 01:16:46,566
We're talking about the same great taste...

1121
01:16:46,567 --> 01:16:47,567
same great taste, while
boosting the bottom line.

1122
01:16:47,568 --> 01:16:51,070
It's called a milkshake Ray.

1123
01:16:51,071 --> 01:16:52,058
Real milk.

1124
01:16:52,059 --> 01:16:53,361
Now and forever!

1125
01:16:54,067 --> 01:16:55,229
I understa...

1126
01:17:17,400 --> 01:17:19,580
I'm just asking you to extend my line.

1127
01:17:19,581 --> 01:17:23,025
Until you build more equity in your
home or pay down the loan...

1128
01:17:23,026 --> 01:17:24,018
there's nothing I can do.

1129
01:17:24,019 --> 01:17:26,747
- My business is booming.
- Unfortunately that's immaterial.

1130
01:17:26,748 --> 01:17:28,821
Well, I've got 13 locations in 9 states...

1131
01:17:28,822 --> 01:17:30,560
It's a home equity loan.

1132
01:17:30,561 --> 01:17:31,688
Then give me a business loan.

1133
01:17:31,689 --> 01:17:34,110
- These 13 locations, do you own 'em?
- Me personally?

1134
01:17:34,111 --> 01:17:36,059
It's your business, correct?
You own it.

1135
01:17:36,060 --> 01:17:37,554
I'm the head of franchising.

1136
01:17:37,979 --> 01:17:40,937
I'm the one behind this growth.

1137
01:17:40,938 --> 01:17:42,643
That's all well and good
but you need assets.

1138
01:17:44,564 --> 01:17:45,991
Have you been to a McDonald's?

1139
01:17:45,992 --> 01:17:49,921
Because we've got 3 right here in the Chicagoland
area and you should come by and take a look.

1140
01:17:49,922 --> 01:17:53,108
I would love to give you a tour to give
you a better sense of what I'm talking about.

1141
01:17:56,392 --> 01:17:57,185
Mr. Kroc...

1142
01:17:58,260 --> 01:17:59,228
May I help you?

1143
01:17:59,854 --> 01:18:03,271
No, but... perhaps I can help you.

1144
01:18:03,603 --> 01:18:05,113
Harry Sonneborn, nice to meet you.

1145
01:18:06,013 --> 01:18:09,045
No, thanks.
We're very happy with our current supplier.

1146
01:18:09,512 --> 01:18:10,933
I'm not here to sell you ice cream.

1147
01:18:11,235 --> 01:18:12,539
What the hell do ya want?

1148
01:18:12,540 --> 01:18:16,010
I caught a bit of your conversation back there,
sounds like you're having financial troubles.

1149
01:18:16,344 --> 01:18:17,548
Why don't you mind your own business?

1150
01:18:17,549 --> 01:18:19,462
I'm a great admirer of your establishment.

1151
01:18:21,178 --> 01:18:23,968
- Thank you.
- I eat lunch at your Waukegan location at least twice a week.

1152
01:18:24,329 --> 01:18:25,699
Always a fantastic crowd.

1153
01:18:26,061 --> 01:18:27,261
Your point being...

1154
01:18:27,262 --> 01:18:32,200
Mr. Kroc, if you're not making money hand over fist,
something's terribly wrong.

1155
01:18:36,552 --> 01:18:38,311
June, grab the ledger would ya?

1156
01:18:39,315 --> 01:18:40,551
Come on in the office Harry.

1157
01:18:52,831 --> 01:18:56,741
So, to summerize,
you have a miniscule revenue stream...

1158
01:18:56,742 --> 01:18:57,926
no cash reserves...

1159
01:18:57,927 --> 01:18:59,880
amd an albatross of a contract...

1160
01:18:59,881 --> 01:19:02,173
that requires you to go through
a slow approval process to...

1161
01:19:02,174 --> 01:19:04,249
enact changes, if they're approved at all.

1162
01:19:04,743 --> 01:19:05,825
Which, they never are.

1163
01:19:06,737 --> 01:19:08,322
Am I missing anything?

1164
01:19:08,323 --> 01:19:09,619
That about sums it up.

1165
01:19:10,929 --> 01:19:12,518
Tell me about the land.

1166
01:19:12,519 --> 01:19:14,132
The... land.

1167
01:19:14,133 --> 01:19:17,267
The land, the buildings, how
that whole aspect of it works.

1168
01:19:17,488 --> 01:19:19,197
Oh, pretty simple really...

1169
01:19:19,198 --> 01:19:21,617
franchisee finds a piece of land he likes...

1170
01:19:21,840 --> 01:19:23,710
gets a lease, usually 20 years...

1171
01:19:23,711 --> 01:19:25,472
and takes our construction loan...

1172
01:19:26,450 --> 01:19:28,396
throws up a building
and off he goes.

1173
01:19:30,082 --> 01:19:32,331
So the operator selects the site?

1174
01:19:32,332 --> 01:19:34,503
- Yeah.
- He picks the property.

1175
01:19:34,504 --> 01:19:35,260
Right.

1176
01:19:35,261 --> 01:19:38,452
You provide the training, the system,
the operational know how...

1177
01:19:38,453 --> 01:19:41,601
and he is responsible for the rest.

1178
01:19:42,378 --> 01:19:43,880
- Is there a problem?
- A big one.

1179
01:19:44,369 --> 01:19:46,546
You don't seem to realize
what business you're in.

1180
01:19:48,514 --> 01:19:50,590
You're not in the burger business,

1181
01:19:50,591 --> 01:19:52,665
you're in the real estate business.

1182
01:19:54,657 --> 01:20:01,053
You don't build an empire off a 1.4% cut
of a $0.15 hamburger.

1183
01:20:01,697 --> 01:20:04,496
You build it by owning the land...

1184
01:20:04,497 --> 01:20:06,689
upon which that burger is cooked.

1185
01:20:07,579 --> 01:20:09,268
What you ought to be doing...

1186
01:20:09,269 --> 01:20:11,185
is buying up plots of land...

1187
01:20:11,186 --> 01:20:14,960
then turning around and leasing
said plots to franchisees.

1188
01:20:14,961 --> 01:20:16,543
Who as a condition of their deal...

1189
01:20:16,544 --> 01:20:20,018
should be permitted to lease from you,
and you alone.

1190
01:20:20,849 --> 01:20:22,821
This will provide you with two things.

1191
01:20:22,822 --> 01:20:25,473
1. A steady up front revenue stream...

1192
01:20:25,474 --> 01:20:26,474
money flows in before the
first stake is in the ground.

1193
01:20:26,475 --> 01:20:31,497
2. Greater capital for expansion.

1194
01:20:31,498 --> 01:20:34,183
Which in turn fuels further land aquisition...

1195
01:20:34,184 --> 01:20:36,253
which in turn fuels further expansion...

1196
01:20:36,254 --> 01:20:38,707
and so on, and so on.

1197
01:20:42,833 --> 01:20:44,113
Land.

1198
01:20:46,415 --> 01:20:48,087
That's where the money is.

1199
01:20:48,088 --> 01:20:50,318
And more than that, control.

1200
01:20:51,569 --> 01:20:54,296
Control over the franchisee.

1201
01:20:54,297 --> 01:20:58,198
Fail to uphold quality standards,
you cancel their lease.

1202
01:20:59,483 --> 01:21:02,842
Control over Dick and Mac.

1203
01:21:03,078 --> 01:21:07,846
End result, you'll have the banks and the
franchisees in the palm of your hand.

1204
01:21:09,004 --> 01:21:12,915
If I were to do this, the brothers,
they uh...

1205
01:21:15,582 --> 01:21:19,473
- effectively would be...
- Yes.

1206
01:21:22,958 --> 01:21:23,697
So...

1207
01:21:25,505 --> 01:21:27,252
What do you say Ray?

1208
01:21:43,361 --> 01:21:47,995
We'll need backing. I've arranged meetings
with investors and financial institutions.

1209
01:21:47,996 --> 01:21:51,199
The center of town which is the
only oversaturated aspect...

1210
01:21:53,694 --> 01:21:56,047
Has anyone here ever eaten at McDonald's?

1211
01:21:56,048 --> 01:21:58,237
This population growth is
going to enable us to expand...

1212
01:22:00,644 --> 01:22:03,931
The figures are exaggerated but they're
fully supported by the numericals.

1213
01:22:03,932 --> 01:22:06,313
In fact, we erred on the side of caution with these.

1214
01:22:06,314 --> 01:22:06,860
He's being conservative.

1215
01:22:06,861 --> 01:22:10,367
Mine, based on gut, and my gut
tells me those numbers are low.

1216
01:22:10,368 --> 01:22:12,536
McDonald's, growing quick as a hick.

1217
01:22:12,537 --> 01:22:14,640
I'm Harry Sonneborn, this is Ray Kroc.

1218
01:22:14,675 --> 01:22:18,483
Hurry over to McDonald's.
Now serving family communities from coast to coast.

1219
01:22:18,749 --> 01:22:22,992
You're probably only minutes away
from America's favorite restaurant.

1220
01:22:24,083 --> 01:22:27,486
McDonald's fast service is the
perfect answer for parties,

1221
