01:40:29,020 --> 01:40:33,411
Just, grab your ideas and run off,
start my own business...

1466
01:40:33,412 --> 01:40:35,188
using all those ideas of yours.

1467
01:40:35,189 --> 01:40:36,868
- It would have failed.
- How do you know?

1468
01:40:36,869 --> 01:40:39,142
Am I the only one who got the kitchen tour?

1469
01:40:39,143 --> 01:40:42,108
You must have invited lots
of people back there, huh?

1470
01:40:42,109 --> 01:40:43,259
And?

1471
01:40:43,267 --> 01:40:45,048
How many of them succeeded?

1472
01:40:45,780 --> 01:40:47,531
Lots of people started restaurants.

1473
01:40:47,532 --> 01:40:48,571
As big as McDonald's?

1474
01:40:48,572 --> 01:40:49,660
Of course not.

1475
01:40:49,802 --> 01:40:55,364
No one ever has and no one ever will
because they all lacked that one thing...

1476
01:40:56,089 --> 01:40:57,833
that makes McDonald's special.

1477
01:40:57,834 --> 01:40:58,731
Which is?

1478
01:41:01,038 --> 01:41:03,237
Even you don't know what it is.

1479
01:41:03,238 --> 01:41:04,300
Enlighten me.

1480
01:41:05,759 --> 01:41:08,225
It's not just the system, Dick.

1481
01:41:09,014 --> 01:41:10,034
It's the name.

1482
01:41:10,585 --> 01:41:13,063
That glorious name, McDonald's.

1483
01:41:13,584 --> 01:41:17,293
It could be, anything you want it to be...

1484
01:41:17,294 --> 01:41:19,312
it's limitless, it's wide open...

1485
01:41:19,313 --> 01:41:21,345
it sounds, uh...

1486
01:41:21,936 --> 01:41:23,320
it sounds like...

1487
01:41:23,888 --> 01:41:25,606
it sounds like America.

1488
01:41:26,789 --> 01:41:29,660
That's compared to Kroc. What a crock.
What a load of crock.

1489
01:41:29,661 --> 01:41:35,118
Would you eat at a place named Kroc's?
Kroc's has that blunt, Slavic sound.

1490
01:41:35,119 --> 01:41:36,097
Kroc's.

1491
01:41:36,098 --> 01:41:38,575
But McDonald's, oh boy.

1492
01:41:38,576 --> 01:41:39,461
That's a beauty.

1493
01:41:40,347 --> 01:41:42,150
Yeah...

1494
01:41:42,733 --> 01:41:44,840
A guy named McDonald?

1495
01:41:46,189 --> 01:41:48,497
He's never gonna get pushed around in life.

1496
01:41:49,953 --> 01:41:51,769
That's clearly not the case.

1497
01:41:51,770 --> 01:41:57,695
So, you don't have a check for
1.35 million dollars in your pocket?

1498
01:42:03,189 --> 01:42:04,674
Bye Dick.

1499
01:42:05,500 --> 01:42:08,073
So if you can't beat 'em, buy 'em.

1500
01:42:10,922 --> 01:42:15,792
I remember the first time I saw that name
stretched across your stand out there.

1501
01:42:17,032 --> 01:42:18,643
It was love at first sight.

1502
01:42:18,644 --> 01:42:21,327
I knew right then and there...

1503
01:42:22,036 --> 01:42:23,518
I had to have it.

1504
01:42:25,920 --> 01:42:27,190
And now I do.

1505
01:42:27,562 --> 01:42:29,268
You don't, have it.

1506
01:42:32,762 --> 01:42:34,046
You sure about that?

1507
01:42:37,456 --> 01:42:38,374
Bye Dick.

1508
01:42:46,214 --> 01:42:51,281
As per the terms of your agreement, while you
are entitled to maintain ownership of this location...

1509
01:42:51,628 --> 01:42:55,831
you no longer have the right to call it, McDonald's,
McDonald, or any other such variations...

1510
01:42:55,832 --> 01:42:58,896
so as to confuse or infringe
upon the McDonald's trademark...

1511
01:42:59,380 --> 01:43:02,738
which is now the exclusive intellectual
property of Mr. Raymond A. Kroc.

1512
01:43:02,739 --> 01:43:03,511
Thank you gentlemen.

1513
01:43:25,058 --> 01:43:26,154
It'll be alright.

1514
01:43:35,664 --> 01:43:38,677
Now, I know what you're thinkin'.

1515
01:43:39,286 --> 01:43:44,666
How the hell does a 52 year old,
over-the-hill milkshake machine salesman...

1516
01:43:44,667 --> 01:43:51,150
build a fastfood empire with 16,000 restaurants,
in 50 states, in 5 foreign countries...

1517
01:43:51,151 --> 01:43:56,311
wtih an annual revenue of in the
neighborhood of $700,000,000.00...

1518
01:43:57,764 --> 01:43:58,781
One word...

1519
01:43:59,834 --> 01:44:01,575
PERSISTENCE.

1520
01:44:06,397 --> 01:44:10,784
Nothing in this world can take
the place of good old persistence.

1521
01:44:11,292 --> 01:44:16,800
Talent won't. Nothing's more common
than unsuccessful men with talent.

1522
01:44:17,589 --> 01:44:18,923
Genius won't.

1523
01:44:19,736 --> 01:44:22,489
Unrecognized genius is practically a cliché.

1524
01:44:22,490 --> 01:44:24,192
Education won't.

1525
01:44:24,193 --> 01:44:27,105
Why the world is full of educated fools.

1526
01:44:27,244 --> 01:44:31,969
Persistence and determination
alone are all powerful.

1527
01:44:49,006 --> 01:44:52,116
Mr. Kroc., Bill Davison.

1528
01:44:52,117 --> 01:44:55,622
I'd like to do a profile of you
pegged to your 100th location.

1529
01:44:55,623 --> 01:44:57,438
Sure, call my office.

1530
01:44:58,387 --> 01:44:59,098
Sure thing.

1531
01:45:00,048 --> 01:45:00,829
Alright.

1532
01:45:11,306 --> 01:45:13,468
It's these core principles...

1533
01:45:13,469 --> 01:45:16,041
that enabled me to rise to the top of a heap...

1534
01:45:16,042 --> 01:45:20,457
at a point in life when most men
would be thinking about retirement.

1535
01:45:20,791 --> 01:45:23,531
Why, we appear to have that in common,
governer Reagan.

1536
01:45:23,532 --> 01:45:27,167
Why, you were what, 55
when you started in politics?

1537
01:45:27,945 --> 01:45:30,866
That's why you make me
look like a spring chicken.

1538
01:45:30,867 --> 01:45:32,568
Laugh, laugh, laugh.

1539
01:45:33,035 --> 01:45:36,172
Why, look at us.
A couple of Illinois boys.

1540
01:45:36,173 --> 01:45:39,247
Made good.
Only in America.

1541
01:45:41,283 --> 01:45:43,072
Only in America.

1542
01:45:43,073 --> 01:45:44,600
Only in America!

1543
01:45:45,599 --> 01:45:47,919
Now where was...
Now where was I?

1544
01:45:47,920 --> 01:45:50,298
Ah yes.

1545
01:45:50,299 --> 01:45:51,374
The beginning.

1546
01:45:51,987 --> 01:45:54,572
The year was 1954.

1547
01:45:56,110 --> 01:45:57,406
The place...

1548
01:45:58,321 --> 01:45:59,712
Des Plaines, Illinois.

1549
01:46:00,321 --> 01:46:02,000
The car's out front now.

1550
01:46:02,001 --> 01:46:03,438
Be right down.

1551
01:46:28,987 --> 01:46:30,293
That's where it all started.

1552
01:46:33,599 --> 01:46:35,759
Right there on Lee Street.

1553
01:46:38,276 --> 01:46:39,855
McDonald's #1.

1554
01:47:09,716 --> 01:47:13,905
It was a typical, English American word...

1555
01:47:13,906 --> 01:47:16,121
it flowed, McDonald's.

1556
01:47:16,122 --> 01:47:19,233
I liked the sound of it.
It sounded wholesome...

1557
01:47:19,234 --> 01:47:20,946
and it sounded geniune.

1558
01:47:20,947 --> 01:47:21,879
Ya know?

1559
01:47:22,241 --> 01:47:27,634
Uh... I don't like these uh...
gimmick type names, you know?

1560
01:47:28,827 --> 01:47:33,628
Uh... burger this and burger that
and all that kind of stuff.

1561
01:47:33,752 --> 01:47:37,466
McDonald's has got a nice sounding name.

